### Description

I know that Signal API is still developer-preview. If it should be go to discussion part, let me know.

I read all Signal RFC & trying to use Signal for our translation library.

We forked `@ngx-translate/core` and customize its structure into Signal-based pipe. 
https://gist.github.com/leo6104/1d8da771f1cb3da237ca3ba06fe4fdea#file-translate-pipe-ts 

And it shows error message that is out of control range from developer. It would be some point that can be improved (show other error message or support `WritableSignal.set` in Pipe `transform` function.)

### Please provide a link to a minimal reproduction of the bug

Here is minimal reproduction code from the library code. 

```
import { ChangeDetectorRef, effect, EnvironmentInjector, Pipe, runInInjectionContext, signal } from '@angular/core';

@Pipe({
  name: 'test',
  standalone: true,
})
export class TestPipe {
  private value = signal<string>('');
  private lastKey = signal<string>(null);

  constructor() {
    effect((onCleanup) => {
      const key = this.lastKey();

      this.value.set(key + ' world');
    }, { allowSignalWrites: true });
  }

  transform(_query: string | number, ...args: any[]): any {
    const query = (typeof _query === 'number') ? `${_query}` : _query;
    this.lastKey.set(query);
    return this.value();
  }
}

@Component({
   selector: 'app',
   template: `{{ 'hello' | test }}`,
})
export AppComponent {
}
```

With above code, i thought it should print `hello world` but it raise error. we cannot give `allowSignalWrites` to true because we didn't use `computed/effect` in transform function. 


